{{ingredient}}

'''Okara''' is a spongy, crumbly by-product of the [[Cookbook:Soy Milk|soy milk]] and [[Cookbook:Tofu|tofu]]-making process.  While it is edible, it has little nutritional value and doesn't appeal to the palates of most people.

However, it can be made both more palatable and more nutritious by fermenting into ''tempe gembus'', a form of [[Cookbook:Tempeh|tempeh]] made from okara.

